Description: Fragment of a small seal-impression made of fine brown Nile clay that was hardened after excavation and shows darker discolouration with a partly glossy surface. The rear shows two deeply impressed turned cords with a width of 0.2 cm perpendicular to the impression of some organic material like wood or basketry. The front has a small flat area with downwards bent sides. On the flat area parts of an oval scarab-like seal-impression. Visible is a thin circumferential line. In the centre a cartouche with Mn-kheper-R' and on each side of it a small winged scarab rotated with its heads towards the cartouche. Same seal on EA86819, EA86897 and EA86899.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
